ry modern cuisine in that it gives pride of place to the essential flavors of its ingredients. In this only English-language book to encompass the entire region, the award-winning author of Encyclopedia of Pasta, Oretta Zanini De Vita, offers a substantial and complex social history of Rome and Lazio through the story of its food. Including more than 250 authentic, easy-to-follow recipes, the author leads readers on an exhilarating journey from antiquity through the Middle Ages to the mid-twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCooking, Roman. 0aDinners and diningxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  acookbook.  acookbooks.  acooking made easy.  acooking.  aculinary history.  aculinary.  acustoms.  aeasy to read.  aengaging.  aenthic foods.  aessential flavors.  afood and wine.  afood lovers.  afood prep.  afrugal people.  aherbs.  ahistorical.  ahistory of italian cooking.  ahistory.  ahow to cook.  aitalian cooking.  aitalian food.  aitalian history.  akitchen setting.  alamb.  alazio.  alively.  amodern cuisine.  aolive oil.  aordinary people.  apage turner.  apork.  arecipes.  aregional cooking.  aregional interest.  aretrospective.  aricotta.  arome.  asocial history.  asocial sciences.  atraditions.1 aDi Renzo, Ernesto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFant, Maureen B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027154840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095539440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520955394423Coveruhttps://www.